<isis lang="en">
    <stitle>ELECTRICAL SYSTEM TROUBLESHOOTING GUIDE / 5000 9100 9200 9400 9900 MODELS BUILT OCTOBER 1, 1998 AND AFTER -
        GAUGES AND WARNING LIGHTS - 5000, 5000i, 9000, 9000i - TROUBLESHOOTING - ENGINE EXHAUST TEMPERATURE (PYROMETER)
    </stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="troubleshoot" graphiccount="0">
        <title>ENGINE EXHAUST TEMPERATURE (PYROMETER)</title>
        <svcprocinfo>
            <para>Refer to
                <hotlnk document="s08207x_19.xml" xrefid="x0820714">PYROMETER</hotlnk>
                for circuit operation.
            </para>
        </svcprocinfo>
        <svcsubproc>
            <title>Pyrometer Reads Full Scale With Key ON</title>
            <para>If the circuits to the Pyrometer control module have an open circuit (thermocouple burns out for
                example), the control module produces a full scale signal to the gauge.
            </para>
            <table id="t0820728" tblwidth="full-page" frame="all" numbered="no" view="reveal">
                <title>Pyrometer Reads Full Scale With Key ON</title>
                <tgroup cols="7" colsep="1" rowsep="1" align="center" charoff="50">
                    <colspec colname="1" colwidth="0.48in"/>
                    <colspec colname="2" colwidth="0.50in"/>
                    <colspec colname="3" colwidth="1.72in"/>
                    <colspec colname="4" colwidth="0.75in"/>
                    <colspec colname="5" colwidth="0.75in"/>
                    <colspec colname="6" colwidth="0.80in"/>
                    <colspec colname="7" colwidth="1.67in"/>
                    <tbody valign="top">
                        <row>
                            <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                                <para>
                                    <emph type="bold">STEP</emph>
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                                <para>
                                    <emph type="bold">KEY</emph>
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                                <para>
                                    <emph type="bold">ACTION</emph>
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                                <para>
                                    <emph type="bold">TEST POINTS</emph>
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                                <para>
                                    <emph type="bold">SPEC.</emph>
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                                <para>
                                    <emph type="bold">YES - IN SPEC.</emph>
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                                <para>
                                    <emph type="bold">NO - OUT OF SPEC.</emph>
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                                <para>1.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                                <para>Off</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry rotate="0">
                                <para>Disconnect thermocouple leads from the module at connector (492). Measure
                                    resistance to ground at the 16 gauge red and the yellow wires.
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry rotate="0">
                                <para>16 gauge red and yellow wires to gnd.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry rotate="0">
                                <para>> or = 100K ohms.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry rotate="0">
                                <para>Go to next step.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry rotate="0">
                                <para>Replace the thermocouple/lead assembly.</para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                                <para>2.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                                <para>Off</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry rotate="0">
                                <para>At connector (492), measure the resistance between the red and yellow wires in the
                                    thermocouple assembly.
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry rotate="0">
                                <para>Red and yellow wires.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry rotate="0">
                                <para>3 to 4 ohms.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry rotate="0">
                                <para>Replace the pyrometer control module.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry rotate="0">
                                <para>Replace the thermocouple assembly.</para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                    </tbody>
                </tgroup>
            </table>
        </svcsubproc>
        <svcsubproc>
            <title>Pyrometer Reads LOW Or NO Exhaust Temperature</title>
            <para>Refer to
                <hotlnk document="s08207x_19.xml" xrefid="x0820714">PYROMETER</hotlnk>
                for circuit operation.
            </para>
            <table id="t0820729">
                <title>Pyrometer Reads LOW Or NO Exhaust Temperature</title>
                <tgroup cols="7" colsep="1" rowsep="1">
                    <colspec colname="sqcolumn1" colwidth="0.50in"/>
                    <colspec colname="sqcolumn2" colwidth="0.60in"/>
                    <colspec colname="sqcolumn3" colwidth="1.52in"/>
                    <colspec colname="sqcolumn4" colwidth="0.88in"/>
                    <colspec colname="sqcolumn5" colwidth="0.88in"/>
                    <colspec colname="sqcolumn6" colwidth="0.89in"/>
                    <colspec colname="sqcolumn7" colwidth="1.40in"/>
                    <thead valign="top">
                        <row>
                            <entry>
                                <para>
                                    <emph type="bold">STEP</emph>
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>
                                    <emph type="bold">KEY</emph>
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry align="center">
                                <para>
                                    <emph type="bold">ACTION</emph>
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry align="center">
                                <para>
                                    <emph type="bold">TEST POINTS</emph>
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry align="center">
                                <para>
                                    <emph type="bold">SPEC.</emph>
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry align="center">
                                <para>
                                    <emph type="bold">YES - IN SPEC.</emph>
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry align="center">
                                <para>
                                    <emph type="bold">NO - OUT OF SPEC.</emph>
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                    </thead>
                    <tbody valign="top">
                        <row>
                            <entry>
                                <para>1.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>Off</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>Check 10A fuse F10-A for open condition.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>F10-A.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>Fuse OK.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>Go to next step.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>Locate cause of overload condition, then replace fuse.</para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <entry>
                                <para>2.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>Off/ On</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>Remove conn. (15) from control module. At connector (15) measure voltage to ground
                                    at circuit 25.
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>(15), 25 to gnd.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>10 to 12 volts.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>Go to next step.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>Locate cause of no or low voltage in circuit 25 from fuse F10-A, then repair.
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <entry>
                                <para>3.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>On</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>At connector (15) measure voltage between circuits 25 and 25-G.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>(15), 25 and 25-G.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>10 to 12 volts.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>Go to next step.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>Locate open in circuit 25-G between connector (15) and (454) ground adapter, then
                                    repair.
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <entry>
                                <para>4.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>Off/On</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>Connect (15) to control module and disconnect (423) from gauge cluster. KEY ON-
                                    Measure voltage to ground at connector (423) circuit 25A.
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>(423), 25A to gnd.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>7.7 to 8.7 volts.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>Go to Step 6.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>Go to Step 5.</para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <entry>
                                <para>5.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>On</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>At control module side of connector (15) measure voltage to ground at terminal
                                    blue wire.
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>(15), terminal for blue wire to gnd.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>7.7 to 8.7 volts.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>Locate open in circuit 25A between connectors (15) and (423), then repair.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>Replace control module.</para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <entry>
                                <para>6.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>Off</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>Measure resistance of circuit 25B between connectors (15) and (423).</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>(15) and (423), 25B.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>&#60; or = 5 ohms.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>Go to next step.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>Locate open in circuit 25B, then repair.</para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <entry>
                                <para>7.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>Off</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>At connector (423) measure resistance to ground at circuit 25-GA.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>(423), 25-GA.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>&#60; or = 5 ohms.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>Go to next step.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>Locate open in circuit 25-GA between connector (423) and (454) ground adapter,
                                    then repair.
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <entry>
                                <para>8.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>Off</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>Run engine to generate exhaust temperature. Use thermometer to measure. Measure
                                    voltage to ground at back of connector (15) terminal for brown wire. Refer to the
                                    Chart below for expected voltage.
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>(15), terminal for brown wire.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>Expected voltage.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>Replace the gauge.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>Replace the module.</para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                    </tbody>
                </tgroup>
            </table>
